						               													<description>Welcome to The Druid Master, a tabletop game that will teach you the healing power of medicinal herbs.&amp;#10;An educational fast paced cards game for 1-4 players.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;quot;You are in the middle of the forest, wrapped in the reassuring embrace of nature, and as a Druid you hold and master the ancient art of healing the various ailments, which affect the human body, with the herbs, plants and trees that surround you.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;And so different people will come looking for you who need your help but, beware, you are not alone!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There are also other experienced Druids who compete with you to cure these patients.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;You will have to prove that you can treat them better than your rival Druids, so that you will be proclaimed the one and only Druid Master!&amp;quot;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game consists of 8 rounds where players will have to treat patients with the plants at their disposal.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The plants are represented by cards, which describe the benefits of the plant in percentages.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;7 plant cards are drawn at the beginning of the game and 2 at the beginning of each turn.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;You can use from 1 to 3 plant cards, in combination, to try to cure the patient as much as possible.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;(You can study best combination hidden by the proper player screen)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each turn an event card is drawn that affects all players (famine, harvest day...).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There are also effect cards: one for each player, to be played in the best moment of the game, to take an advantage on the other players or to hinder them.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
